        "title": "feat: add Docker Sandbox provider",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add a provider-neutral `docker-sandbox` delegated-run provider backed by the Docker Sandbox `sbx` CLI.\n- Wire provider config, CLI flags, provider registration, docs, provider discovery metadata, and a live smoke script.\n- Add focused Go tests covering config parsing, provider registration, run/session behavior, command construction, status/stop/doctor flows, error guidance, flags, and mutation-sensitive edge cases.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `git diff --check`\n- `go vet ./...`\n- `go test -count=1 ./internal/cli ./internal/providers/dockersandbox ./internal/providers/all`\n- `go test -race ./...`\n- `scripts/test-go-modules.sh`\n- `scripts/check-go-coverage.sh 90.0` (`Go core coverage 91.0% >= 90.0%`)\n- `go build -trimpath -o bin/crabbox ./cmd/crabbox`\n- `bin/crabbox providers --json | rg '\"name\": \"docker-sandbox\"|\"family\": \"docker-sandbox\"|\"kind\": \"delegated-run\"|\"target\": \"linux\"|\"coordinator\": \"never\"|\"run-session\"|\"local-container\"'`\n- `scripts/check-docs.sh`\n- `node scripts/build-docs-site.mjs`\n- `node --test scripts/*.test.js`\n- `npm ci --prefix worker`\n- `npm run format:check --prefix worker`\n- `npm run lint --prefix worker`\n- `npm run check --prefix worker`\n- `npm test --prefix worker`\n- `npm run build --prefix worker`\n- `go run github.com/go-gremlins/gremlins/cmd/gremlins@latest unleash --diff origin/main --output /tmp/crabbox-docker-sandbox-mutation-coordinator-4.json`\n  - Result: `Killed: 143`, `Lived: 7`, `Not covered: 1`, `Timed out: 0`, `Mutator coverage: 99.34%`.\n  - Remaining survivors are boundary/equivalent-style mutants around no-op/constant/default edge guards after coordinator coverage hardening.\n- `scripts/live-docker-sandbox-smoke.sh`\n  - Result after Docker Sandbox setup: `classification=live_sbx_smoke_passed` with `cleanup=complete`.\n  - Redacted proof: `sbx diagnose` reported `7 passed`; the smoke created a Crabbox-owned `docker-sandbox` lease, ran `echo ok`, ran `pw